job_description:
Data Analysts - professional services within Legal, Risk, Governance

Greenfield opportunity in anindustry-leading firm

£40-70,000 base, up to 20% bonus London

This leading professional services firm provides innovative analytics services to support clients in mitigating operational and commercial risks, including the investigation and prevention of criminal activity and disputes, as well as providing insight analytics to support clients' operational, compliance and regulatory concerns.

Their Data & Risk Advisory practice is experiencing a scale-up phase in its UK operations, and they are hiring analytics practitioners at a number of levels, from second-jobber to team leader. The leastsenior vacancies require require a minimum of two years' professional experience

Their key markets include Banking, TMT, Oil & Gas, Government and Life Sciences, and one of their key differentiators is the harnessing of advanced analytics to enable faster and deeper insights into data. Another is that they lead the market in providing real-world, applicable advice and solutions that are robust and well future-proofed in terms of legal and regulatory requirements.

The roles will require you to:
• Design, build and implement data pipelines, reporting and governance controls;
• Work with clients to understand their business and data, to drive data-driven responses to, for example, compliance breaches and remediation activities;
• Develop algorithms to identify compliance and regulatory risks in client data; use those insights to proactively manage risks;
• Develop insight-driven solutions for clients and showcase the results to their stakeholders;
• Collaborate with other subject-matter experts across the firm to research new fields and apply those learnings to help improve service and strategy;

The successful candidates will have:
• Approximately 2-5 years’ experience in analytics, which will include growing expertise in SOME (it doesn’t need to be all!) of the following: SQL, Alteryx; Tableau; PowerBI; Python;
• Experience of delivering value to clients through: developing data strategies, embedding data governance frameworks, driving insights through analytics, or creating AI/ML-backed solutions;
• The desire and energy to join a high-calibre team with a track record of delivering market-leading advice to clients, and the ambition to continue developing;
• At all levels, you will need to be a creative problem-solver with the ability to communicate effectively with multidisciplinary stakeholders. At the upper levels - c. £60-75k base salary- you will need to show some evidence of line and/or project management

What’s in it for you?
• Working with recognised authorities in analytics, in a relatively greenfield group that is backed by a globally successful professional services firm;
• Using cutting-edge analytics technology and data science techniques;
• Working for a highly successful and ambitious firm, with a highly collaborative, diverse and supportive culture;
• Working on topical projects that matter and impact society as a whole;
• Getting well paid, with generous salaries complemented by great benefits and bonus
